#. type: Plain text
#: 0300-the-georeferencing-process.en.adoc:492
msgid "Harbor charts are generally produced at a scale of 1:10,000, and coastal charts at 1:50,000 to 1:150,000, and often in the Mercator projection. A page on Navigation – finding <<location>> on nautical maps can be seen at http://www.coastalnavigation.com/samples/sec_1/1_pages/1_3.htm[Coastal Navigation 2020^]. A majority of new maps (post-2019) are only being produced digitally (NOAA 2020, personal communication, 25 Jan), with paper maps being produced from the digital product."
