#. type: Plain text
#: 0400-collaborative-georeferencing.en.adoc:4
msgid "The characteristics that make a <<georeference,georeferencing>> project collaborative are the aggregation of occurrence records from multiple participating groups (e.g. datasets, collections, institutions), the extraction of distinct <<locality,localities>> as the actual target of georeferencing, the standardization of the geography of the aggregated records to aid record grouping and assignment by geography."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 0400-collaborative-georeferencing.en.adoc:6
msgid "Collaborative georeferencing, if done properly, can have definitive advantages over georeferencing alone. MaNIS (http://georeferencing.org/georefcalculator/docs/GeorefGuide.html[Wieczorek 2001^]) and Australia's Virtual Herbarium (https://www.anbg.gov.au/chah/avh/avh.html[ANBG 2018^]) found that collaborative georeferencing resulted in great efficiency gains, but that including validation checks afterwards by reviewing the records using collector and date, or looking at the records taxonomically to check for outliers, and other such <<data quality>> flags, is important. Advantages and disadvantages of collaborative georeferencing, adapted from http://georeferencing.org/manis/GeorefCollaboration021021.ppt[Wieczorek & Beaman 2002^] and https://doi.org/10.17161/bi.v1i0.7[Stein & Wieczorek 2004^] include:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 0400-collaborative-georeferencing.en.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Advantages*\n"
msgstr "*Ventajas*\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: 0400-collaborative-georeferencing.en.adoc:10
msgid "Reduces overall cost of supplies (e.g. maps) – no duplication."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 0400-collaborative-georeferencing.en.adoc:11
msgid "Expands the pool of resources – geographic expertise and reference materials."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 0400-collaborative-georeferencing.en.adoc:12
msgid "Takes advantage of regional expertise, knowledge, language skills and resources."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 0400-collaborative-georeferencing.en.adoc:13
msgid "Increases georeferencing rates – economy of scale."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 0400-collaborative-georeferencing.en.adoc:14
msgid "Promotes standardization of methods."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 0400-collaborative-georeferencing.en.adoc:15
msgid "Increases skills in a community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 0400-collaborative-georeferencing.en.adoc:16
msgid "Increases exposure and awareness inside and outside of a community － strengthens community relationships."
